summary:
I hold a bachelor's degree in English Language and Literature and an MA degree in Linguistic and Literary Studies from the Federal University of Santa Catarina, Brazil. In the Netherlands, I have completed a Research Master's degree in Literary Studies at Leiden University. At present, I am a PhD candidate at the Centre for the Arts in Society at Leiden University. My research interests encompass Literature, Cultural Studies, and Cinema with great concern for Post-structuralist approaches, namely, Gender studies, Masculinities, Schizoanalysis, Intersectionality, and Postcolonial theory.

Apart from my scholarly activities, I have been working as an English and Drama teacher. I hold ample experience with different teaching environments and methodological approaches. Through my practice, I seek to achieve the following objectives:
